Now we find the equation of the line passing through $A(4, 0)$ with a gradient of $-\frac{1}{3}$. We can use the point-gradient formula from the data booklet:

$$y - y_1 = m(x - x_1)$$

Substituting our values:

$$
\begin{aligned}
y - 0 &= -\frac{1}{3}(x - 4) \\
y &= -\frac{1}{3}x + \frac{4}{3}
\end{aligned}
$$
